266. Palindrome Permutation

Given a string, determine if a permutation of the string could form a palindrome.

The number of characters with odd number of occurences can't exceed 1 to be a palindrome.

One PASS
Time O(n), 
Space O(n) / O(128) ASCII characters from 0 to 127

bool canPermutePalindrome(string s) {
    int count = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
        m[s[i]]++;
        if (m[s[i]] % 2 == 0) {
            count--;
        } else {
            count++;
        }
    }
    return (count <= 1);
}
private:
unordered_map<char, int> m;


